{
  "texts": [
    "While LLMs are powerful out-of-the-box tools, their full potential can be utilized through fine-tuning, which adapts them to particular tasks beyond their initial training scope.",
    "LLMs excel at interpreting natural language instructions and executing tasks with a proficiency comparable to human performance [29][30][31][32].",
    "The input text provided to an LLM serves as a 'prompt' within what is known as the 'context window' the active field where the model processes information.",
    "Utilizing LLMs to generate text, a process termed 'inference,' relies on the foundational technique of next-word prediction, which supports many of their diverse text-generating tasks [33][34][35][36].",
    "In the context of LLMs, the term 'completion' signifies the output generated, which may encompass more than just single-word predictions and often constitutes full sentences or even paragraphs in response to given prompts.Through fine-tuning and the prompt engineering, LLMs can be informed about specific tasks that are not covered during pretraining, thus empowering them to interact effectively with realworld scenarios."
  ]
}